<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8" standalone="yes"?>
<bug>
    <id>297707</id>
    <title>Color change in the middle of an Arabic word disconnects letters</title>
    <description>
        <paragraph id="1">
            <sentence id="1.1">User-Agent:       Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.7.6) Gecko/20050225 Firefox/1.0.1
Build Identifier: Mozilla/5.0 (Windows; U; Windows NT 5.1; en-US; rv:1.7.6) Gecko/20050225 Firefox/1.0.1</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="2">
            <sentence id="2.1">When the color is changed in the middle of an Arabic word in HTML by using for
instance &lt;font color="red"&gt; letters that normally connect disconnect from each
other.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.2">Internet Explorer has handled this correctly for a number of years.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.3">Please fix this in Firefox as well.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.4">When color changes in the middle of an
Arabic word, it shouldn't disconnect letters, it should rather color them
individually as found in this example for instance:
http://www.submission.org/quran/reader/arabic/v-02A.htm
You will notice the difference if you view this link with Internet Explorer vs.
Firefox.</sentence>
            <sentence id="2.5">Firefox unfortunately disconnects the letters.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="3">
            <sentence id="3.1">Reproducible: Always</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="4">
            <sentence id="4.1">Steps to Reproduce:</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.2">1 Go to http://www.submission.org/quran/reader/arabic/v-02A.htm</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.3">2 Compare Internet Explorer vs. Firefox</sentence>
            <sentence id="4.4">3</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="5">
            <sentence id="5.1">Actual Results:  
Connecting Arabic letters are disconnected.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
        <paragraph id="6">
            <sentence id="6.1">Expected Results:  
It should not have disconnected the Arabic letters.</sentence>
        </paragraph>
    </description>
</bug>
